This is a late review.  I was there about 8 years ago when I was 60 and have been thinking about this place ever since.  I had a slice of plain cheese pizza.  It slowly dawned on me as I ate it, that "this is good pizza," no, "this is Really good pizza," no, that's not it either, " whoa, this is the best pizza I have Ever had."  Dang. I specifically recall asking myself, "Why am I just now, at the advanced age of 60, finding such great pizza?"  I was a little P.O.ed! The crust was somehow chewy and crusty at the same time.  Mystical. There was JUST the right amount of sauce and cheese.  Everything was in perfect balance, the crust, cheese, and wonderful sauce. No one ingredient drowned out the other and no ingredient was skimpy.  It was almost a religious experience.  Perrrfect. Who knows? Maybe I just walked in on a lucky day.  Maybe the planets were lined up just so.  Maybe I was just hungry and concrete might have tasted good.  I'll never know.  I was just visiting the City and never got back to Majestic Pizza.  I live in Florida and am so jealous of you New Yorkers who live or work near this place. I guess I'll give it 5 stars. And Best of Show.
